quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  18,91,"Thus.{1} And We had encompassed [all] that he had in knowledge.",footnotes:1:[Such was the affair of Dhul-Qarnayn.]
  18,92,"Then he followed a way."
  18,93,"Until, when he reached [a pass] between two mountains, he found beside them a people who could hardly understand [his] speech."
  19,52,"And We called him from the side of the mount{1} at [his] right and brought him near, confiding [to him].",footnotes:1:[Mount Sinai.]
  19,53,"And We gave him out of Our mercy his brother Aaron as a prophet."
  19,54,"And mention in the Book, Ishmael. Indeed, he was true to his promise, and he was a messenger and a prophet."
  20,34,"And remember You much."
  20,35,"Indeed, You are of us ever Seeing."
  20,36,"[Allāh] said, "
  21,10,"We have certainly sent down to you a Book [i.e., the Qur’ān] in which is your mention.{1} Then will you not reason?",footnotes:1:[This implies the honor of having been mentioned or addressed.  Another meaning is "your reminder."]
  21,11,"And how many a city which was unjust{1} have We shattered and produced after it another people.",footnotes:1:[i.e., its inhabitants persisting in wrongdoing.]
  21,12,"And when they [i.e., its inhabitants] perceived Our punishment, at once they fled from it."